ascend /əˈsɛnd/

(ascending,ascended,ascends) 

1. V-T If you ascend a hill or staircase, you go up it. 上 (山、楼梯) [书面] 

例： Mrs. Clayton had to hold Lizzie's hand as they ascended the steps. 上台阶时克莱顿夫人不得不抓着莉齐的手。 

2. V-I If a staircase or path ascends , it leads up to a higher position. (楼梯或路) 向上延伸 [书面] 

例： A number of staircases ascend from the cobbled streets onto the ramparts. 若干个阶梯从鹅卵石街道向上延伸到城墙上。 

3. V-I If something ascends , it moves up, usually vertically or into the air. (通常垂直地) 向上移动 [书面] 

例： Keep the drill centred in the borehole while it ascends and descends. 当钻头上下钻时，要把钻孔保持在中心。 

4.  →  see also ascending

